before.enText: of an animal or a vehicle

data.enText: not under the control of its owner, rider or driver

data.chText: 轻易的；迅速的；难以控制的
data.enText: happening very easily or quickly, and not able to be controlled

data.chText: 轻易获胜的人；轻而易举的胜利
她的第一出戏的大获成功
data.enText: the runaway success of her first play

data.chText: 逃跑者，逃避者，离家出走者（尤指儿童）
data.enText: a person who has suddenly left or escaped from sb/sth, especially a child who has left home without telling anyone

data.chText: 流落街头的离家出走的青少年
data.enText: teenage runaways living on the streets

word_means: 逃跑者，逃避者，离家出走者

means: 逃跑者，逃避者，离家出走者(尤指儿童)

tr: someone who flees from an uncongenial situation

value.def: You use runaway to describe a situation in which something increases or develops very quickly and cannot be controlled.

example.ex: Our Grand Sale in June was a runaway success.
example.tran: 我们6月份的大型促销一举成功。

value.tran: 迅速的;无法控制的;失控的

value.def: A runaway is someone, especially a child, who leaves home without telling anyone or without permission.

example.tran: 离家出走的十几岁的孩子

value.def: A runaway vehicle or animal is moving forward quickly, and its driver or rider has lost control of it.

example.ex: The runaway car careered into a bench, hitting an elderly couple...
example.tran: 那辆失控的车猛冲到一条长椅上，撞伤了一对老夫妇。

example.ex: The narrative pulls you along like a runaway train.
example.tran: 这个故事就像一辆失控的高速列车，读起来惊险刺激。
